{"title":"The 2024 Salsa Cutthroat Gets Updates","link":"https://theradavist.com/2024-salsa-cutthroat-gets-updates/","date":1720540800000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5978.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5978.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5978.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5978.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5978.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Hot off the heels of a Tour Divide second place with Salsa rider Ana Jager, the brand announced three key updates to the popular <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/?s=Cutthroat\" target=\"_blank\">Cutthroat</a> touring bike. Let’s check it out below.</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_01.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_01.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_01.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_01.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_01.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The Salsa Cutthroat is wildly popular for touring routes <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/three-days-on-the-tour-divide-with-the-salsa-cutthroat/\" target=\"_blank\">like the Tour Divide</a> as well as the more common bike camping trips and <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/santa-fe-aspen-ranch-overnighter/\" target=\"_blank\">sub-24-hour-overnighters</a>. These frames are proper <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/1987-steve-potts-signature/\" target=\"_blank\">drop bar mountain bikes</a>, utilizing a high stack, wide drops, and 148/100 mm boost spaced-frames.</p>\n<p><strong>Cutthroat Quick Hits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Clearance for up to 29 × 2.4″ tire in the rear and 29 × 3.0″ in the front for riding exceptionally rugged trails</li>\n<li>Compliant carbon frame and fork smooth out trail impacts</li>\n<li>Suspension corrected for 100mm travel 29″ forks</li>\n<li>Hydraulic disc brakes modulate speed smoothly</li>\n<li>SRAM UDH protects against chain jams and broken rear derailleurs and is widely available</li>\n<li>Dropper post on select models allows for more control in tricky spots</li>\n<li>Frame and fork protection features defend against dings and abrasion</li>\n<li>Suspension corrected for 100mm travel 29″ forks</li>\n<li>12 × 148mm rear spacing</li>\n<li>BB92 press-fit bottom bracket</li>\n<li>27.2 seat post</li>\n<li>IS41/52 headset</li>\n<li>No fender mounts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5694.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5694.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5694.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5694.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/GM1A5694.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>This tried and true platform maintains its old geometry but received a few chassis updates, ensuring the longevity of the carbon frame from heavy use.</p>\n<p><strong>The key updates on this new Cutthroat are:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>SRAM UDH compatibility</li>\n<li>New material on abrasion-resistant frame and fork plates</li>\n<li>Carbon steerer tubes on all models</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cutthroat Rival GX AXS, Price <strong>$5,499</strong> USD</li>\n<li>Cutthroat Frameset, Price <strong>$2,499</strong> USD</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_06.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_06.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_06.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_06.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_06.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_22.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_22.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_22.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_22.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_22.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Cutthroat New Carbon Fork Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>32% more compliant than the original Cutthroat fork</li>\n<li>Updated abrasion-resistant plates in high-wear areas prevent damage from mud buildup and debris</li>\n<li>Backwards-compatible with all Cutthroat frames</li>\n<li>One set of Three-Pack mounts on each fork leg</li>\n<li>Salsa Down Under rack compatibility</li>\n<li>Internal brake hose and dynamo routing</li>\n<li>483mm axle to crown length</li>\n<li>Boost 15 x 110mm hub spacing</li>\n<li>Full carbon with carbon steerer tube</li>\n<li>51mm offset</li>\n<li>Flat-mount brakes</li>\n<li>No fender mounts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_05.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_05.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_05.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_05.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/20240322_SAL_Cutthroat_Teal_05.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Also launching today are updated bags for the Cutthroat and other models:</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0364.jpg?fit=1200,683&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0364.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0364.jpg?resize=1200,410&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0364.jpg?resize=768,262&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0364.jpg?resize=1536,525&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1337\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0366-05.jpg?fit=1200,1337&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0366-05.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0366-05.jpg?resize=1200,802&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0366-05.jpg?resize=768,513&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0366-05.jpg?resize=1536,1027&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The <strong>Cholla Frame Bag </strong>is a versatile half-frame bag with inclusive fit on a wider range of Salsa frames and rider sizes. It’s perfect for stowing ride essentials on a light-and-fast Adventure by Bike on gravel, dirt, and pavement. Price $90 USD.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Direct-mount capable with compatible Salsa frames</li>\n<li>Fits a wide range of non-Salsa frames with included straps</li>\n<li>Inclusive fit with extended size range (six sizes)</li>\n<li>1000D Cordura nylon body with 400D nylon lining</li>\n<li>Durable molded-tooth zippers</li>\n<li>Cut-and-sewn construction</li>\n<li>Drive-side access with non-drive-side slash pocket</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1066\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0372-01.jpg?fit=1200,1066&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0372-01.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0372-01.jpg?resize=1200,640&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0372-01.jpg?resize=768,409&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0372-01.jpg?resize=1536,819&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1514\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0488-01.jpg?fit=1200,1514&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0488-01.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0488-01.jpg?resize=1200,908&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0488-01.jpg?resize=768,581&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0488-01.jpg?resize=1536,1163&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The <strong>Saguaro Seat Bag </strong>is quick-loading, easy to use, and stable over the roughest terrain. Price $120 (md), $140 (lg) USD. The waterproof dry bag keeps gear safe through the worst weather conditions. Price $50 (md, 9L), $55 (lg, 14L) USD.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Holster-style with removable dry bag for easy packing</li>\n<li>Welded waterproof dry bag with air purge valve</li>\n<li>Four-point connection to saddle rails for increased stability</li>\n<li>Dropper post-compatible</li>\n<li>Fits on almost any bike</li>\n<li>Two sizes: Medium (9 liters) and Large (14 liters)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"2407\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370.jpg?fit=1200,2407&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370.jpg?resize=1200,1444&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370.jpg?resize=768,924&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370.jpg?resize=1276,1536&amp;quality=75 1276w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370.jpg?resize=1702,2048&amp;quality=75 1702w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1788\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-02.jpg?fit=1200,1788&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-02.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-02.jpg?resize=1200,1073&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-02.jpg?resize=768,687&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-02.jpg?resize=1536,1373&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"2539\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-01.jpg?fit=1200,2539&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-01.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-01.jpg?resize=1200,1523&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-01.jpg?resize=768,975&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-01.jpg?resize=1210,1536&amp;quality=75 1210w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/BG0370-01.jpg?resize=1613,2048&amp;quality=75 1613w\" /></p>\n<p>The <strong>Agave Pannier </strong>is built for safe storage on pavement and gravel adventure rides. Price $90 USD.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rixen and Kaul hardware for secure rack attachment</li>\n<li>Welded construction with waterproof materials</li>\n<li>Mesh front pocket and reflective side patches</li>\n<li>Designed to avoid heel strike</li>\n<li>Compatible with most racks</li>\n<li>12.5 liter capacity</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://www.salsacycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Salsa</a> and check out our Cutthroat coverage in our Archives below!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2024-salsa-cutthroat-gets-updates/\">The 2024 Salsa Cutthroat Gets Updates</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"b54e76d74d279ea9be627ce5853d24d69b15cc5960473ee0650ea4934ca74ecd","category":"Cycling"}